    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats`\n\n**8 files** to touch — 2 new, 6 modified.\n\n### What's being added\n\n1. **`PreviewFeature::CacheStats = 1 << 28`** in `crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs` — new experimental gate (string: `\"cache-stats\"`)\n\n2. **CLI args** in `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` — `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant on `CacheCommand`, `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct (identical shape to `SizeArgs`)\n\n3. **New handler** `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`:\n   - Iterates `CacheBucket::iter()` (10 buckets: wheels, sdists, flat-index, git, interpreter, simple, archive, builds, environments, binaries)\n   - Calls `cache.bucket(bucket)` → path, then `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` (same `diskus` crate already used by `cache size`)\n   - Prints a two-column table (name padded, size), then a `Total` row\n   - `--human` / `-H` formats via existing `human_readable_bytes()`\n   - **Key gotcha:** `CacheBucket::to_str()` is private — use `bucket.to_string()` (public `Display` impl) instead\n\n4. **Dispatch** in `crates/uv/src/lib.rs` — one new `Commands::Cache(CacheNamespace { command: CacheCommand::Stats(args) })` match arm (sync, same as `Size`)\n\n5. **Test helpers** in `crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs` — `cache_stats()` command builder + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` filter\n\n6. **3 integration tests** in `crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs` + module registration in `main.rs`",
